  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zimbabwe  Private Voluntary Organisations  Act Amendment  Influencing Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In view of the evident threat of shrinking of civic space, Oxfam endeavours to support and work with its partners towards the protection, safeguarding and promotion of civic space which is under huge threat from the proposed Private Voluntary Organisation (PVO) Amendment Bill. Thus, the main objective of this intervention is to enhance the Civil Society Organisations (CSOs) enabling environment in Zimbabwe. The specific objectives of this intervention are to: &#x2022; To strengthen structured coordination and complementarity of CSOs from the different actors, citizens, and thematic sectors of operations ahead of the PVO Amendment Bill public hearings.  &#x2022; To provide an alternative view to the proposed PVO Amendment Bill through popularizing alternative CSO self -regulatory initiatives. &#x2022; Mobilize citizens and CSOs to contribute towards the realisation of an enhanced CSOs enabling environment by massively participating in public hearings for the PVO Amendment Act Bill for safeguarding and promotion of civic space.</narrative>
  </description>
